offey","52506 ; 52511 ; 52512","2016-11-17T15:11:32.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634078/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634078/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-11","Rhinoceros: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions her Department has had with governments in African countries with a rhino population on the survival of that animal in the wild.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","52507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634079","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-11-17","<p>Defra has had no specific discussions with African governments with a population of chimpanzee, gorilla or lowland gorilla on the survival of these animals in the wild. However, the UK is a member of the Great Ape Survival Partnership (GRASP). This is a United Nations initiative committed to ensuring the long term survival of great apes and their habitats in Africa and Asia, which includes chimpanzees and gorillas. Additionally we have funded projects through the Darwin Initiative that have benefitted chimpanzees and gorillas.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","52509 ; 52510","2016-11-17T15:15:28.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634079/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634079/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-11-11","Primates: Africa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions her Department has had with governments in African countries with a chimpanzee population on the survival of that animal in the wild.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","52508"
