re</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-11-16T15:29:08.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634197/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634197/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-11","Department for Transport: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on non-London pay structures in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","52633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634198","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Government has no current plans to review the age of eligibility for an older person’s concessionary bus pass. The age of eligibility for concessionary travel in England is rising in line with the state pension age changes. Equalising the age difference between men and women and increasing the age of entitlement to a concessionary travel pass will remove the anomalous position of non-disabled, working-age citizens receiving free bus passes, which in turn will help the financial sustainability of the scheme.</p><p> </p><p>Concessionary travel is a devolved policy area, so the administrative arrangements in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland differ from those in England. Those differences, including age eligibility, were decided by and are funded by the devolved Governments in Edinburgh, Cardiff and Belfast.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-11-18T09:27:37.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634198/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634198/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-11","Bus Services: Concessions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he plans to review the situation in England whereby the age of eligibility for an older person's bus pass is linked to the female state pension age; and if he will assess the potential merits of bringing such eligibility in line with the rest of the UK.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","52615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634199","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>Although my department does not have specific funding to assist with measures to limit noise from rail lines, Network Rail identifies and mitigates noise impacts as a standard part of its project planning and delivery processes. This includes requiring suppliers to demonstrate that they are designing to minimise the impact of noise and vibration during both construction and operation.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-11-18T10:32:30.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634199/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634199/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-11","Railways: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what funding his Department makes available to assist with measures to limit noise from rail lines.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","52617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634200","Department for Transport","false","2016-11-18","<p>It is a commercial decision for fuel suppliers and retailers whether to provide pumps dispensing Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG). The Department has not made an assessment of the current location of LPG pumps which drivers may access. Drivers of LPG vehicles can obtain information on filling stations supplying LPG in their area from fuel retailers or the trade association UKLPG.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2016-11-18T10:29:06.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634200/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634200/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634200/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-11-11","Liquefied Petroleum Gas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on driver access to LPG pumps of the proposed removal of such pumps from some petrol stations.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","52649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634201","Wales Office","false","2016-11-16","<p>We have no staff on an outer London pay structure.</p><p>Staff in our Whitehall office are on an inner London pay structure, and staff in our Cardiff Office are on a National pay structure.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-11-16T12:27:50.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634201/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634201/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-11-11","Wales Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on an outer London pay structure in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","52634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634202","Wales Office","false","2016-11-17","<p>The Wales Office is a very small department where the majority of women work at our Cardiff Office. The proportion of these women, on the National Plus pay structure (a non-London pay structure), by grade is detailed below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Proportion of Women in Cardiff</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(a) Administrative Assistant</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(b) Administrative Officer</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(c) Executive Officer</p></td><td><p>14%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(d) Higher Executive Officer</p></td><td><p>36%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(e) Fast Streamer</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(f) Senior Executive Officer</p></td><td><p>29%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(g) Grade Seven</p></td><td><p>7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(h) Grade Six</p></td><td><p>14%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(i) Senior Civil Service Band 1</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A</p></td><td><p>no staff employed at this grade</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(k) Senior Civil Service Band 2</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>(l) Senior Civil Service Band 3</p></td><td><p>no staff employed at this grade</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2016-11-17T11:29:40.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634202/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634202/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2016-11-11","Wales Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of women are employed by his Department on non-London pay structures in the following pay grades (a) Administrative Assistant, (b) Administrative Officer, (c) Executive Officer, (d) Higher Executive Officer, (e) Fast Streamer, (f) Senior Executive Officer, (g) Grade Seven, (h) Grade Six, (i) Senior Civil Service Band 1, (j) Senior Civil Service Band 1A, (k) Senior Civil Service Band 2 and (l) Senior Civil Service Band 3.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","52590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634203","Women and Equalities","false","2016-11-18","<p>The number of staff employed by the Department for Education (DfE) and the Government Equalities Office (GEO) in the grades listed above are shown in the table below. The table provides information on the total number of women on Civil Service grades in DfE and GEO and the proportion of them that are paid salaries on the London paybands at each grade. DfE has staff working in a number of regional offices across England. These are included in the totals shown in the table, but are not broken down separately.</p><p>These numbers are based on DfE payroll records and therefore exclude staff joining the department via recent Machinery of Government changes (Higher and Further Education/Skills Funding Agency) as these have yet to transfer onto these systems.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3" rowspan="2"><p>Proportion of all women in the DfE/GEO who are in London paybands at the following grades</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grades</p></td><td><p>1) DfE</p></td><td><p>2) GEO</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total number of women employed (London and National paybands)</p></td><td><p><strong>2264</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>35</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EA AO (equivalent to AO)</p></td><td><p>1%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EO</p></td><td><p>10%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HEO</p></td><td><p>9%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SEO</p></td><td><p>7%</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>GRADE 7</p></td><td><p>11%</p></td><td><p>11%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>GRADE 6</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS Band 1</p></td><td><p>2%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS Band 1A</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS Band 2</p></td><td><p>1%</p></td><td><p>3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS Band 3</p></td><td><p>0%</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2