"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634204","Women and Equalities","false","2016-11-22","<p>I will be happy to provide the hon member with a copy of the updated guidance once it is ready to issue. I will also at that stage place a copy in the Library.</p><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-11-22T11:29:29.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634204/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634204/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2016-11-11","Public Sector: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, pursuant to the Answer of 2 November 2016 to Question 49845, if she will provide a draft copy of the Public Sector Equality Duty guidance to the hon. Member for Brent Central in advance of its wider publication; and if she will place a copy in the Library.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","52654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634205","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-11-16","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>As two people with the same condition can be affected in different ways, there is no condition based entitlement to Employment Support Allowance. The Work Capability Assessment recognises that conditions can vary in their severity and therefore people with the same condition can be placed in the Work Related Activity Group or the Support Group.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-11-16T14:16:38.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634205/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634205/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-11-11","Employment and Support Allowance: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people with degenerative illnesses are included within the employment and support allowance work-related activity group in (a) Plymouth, (b) the South West and (c) England; and whether any special provision is made for people who have degenerative conditions.","false","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","52658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634206","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-11-16","<p>There is no condition based entitlement to Employment Support Allowance.</p><p>Rather than a list of specific medical conditions, the criteria will be based on identifying claimants with the most severe health conditions or disabilities where it would be unreasonable to expect the individual to undertake any form or amount of work or work-related activity. This change will only apply to those placed in the Support Group and Universal Credit equivalent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-11-16T14:32:22.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634206/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634206/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-11-11","Employment and Support Allowance: Chronic Illnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will list the conditions that meet the chronically ill criteria used to exempt claimants from reassessments for employment and support allowance.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","52657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634207","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-11-16","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-11-16T14:41:11.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634207/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/634207/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-11-11","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many new employment and support allowance claimants have been in receipt of the assessment rate for a continuous period of more than 13 weeks in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","52641"
